# Swift file header

Every **new** `.swift` file must start with this block (before any `import`). Do not add headers to `Package.swift` or generated build artifacts under `.build/`.

```swift
//
//  FileName.swift
//  <TargetName>
//
//  Created by Ahsan Minhas on DD/MM/YYYY.
//

```

## Rules

- `FileName.swift` must match the actual file name exactly.
- `<TargetName>`: `QuranDaily` for app sources, `QuranDailyTests` for unit tests, `QuranDailyUITests` for UI tests.
- Use **today's date** (DD/MM/YYYY) when creating a new file; do not change the date when editing an existing file.
- One blank line after the closing `//` before the first `import` or code.
- When editing an existing file that already has a header, leave it unchanged.
